@startuml High School Story — Relationship Arc Template

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #FFF5F7
    BorderColor #D53F8C
    FontSize 11
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFBEB
    BorderColor #D69E2E
    FontSize 10
}

title NPC Relationship Arc — State Diagram (Template)

[*] --> Stranger : Game start / first encounter

state Stranger {
    Stranger : Rel = 0
    Stranger : NPC visible in school but no interaction
}

state "Stage 1\nAcquaintance" as S1 {
    S1 : Rel 0–9
    S1 : First meaningful interaction
    S1 : NPC outer persona shown
    S1 : Player choice sets initial tone
    S1 : Reward: NPC added to phone contacts
}

state "Stage 2\nBudding Friendship" as S2 {
    S2 : Rel 10–24
    S2 : Shared activity / lunch / task
    S2 : NPC shares hobbies or quirks
    S2 : Reward: minor passive stat bonus
}

state "Stage 3\nVulnerability" as S3 {
    S3 : Rel 25–49
    S3 : Catch NPC in a private moment
    S3 : First crack in their outer persona
    S3 : Hidden trait hinted at
    S3 : Reward: unique location or hangout unlocked
}

state "Stage 4\nTrust" as S4 {
    S4 : Rel 50–74
    S4 : NPC initiates a personal conversation
    S4 : Backstory begins unfolding
    S4 : Secret trait partially revealed
    S4 : Reward: custom gift option, item
}

state "Stage 5\nEmotional Climax" as S5 {
    S5 : Rel 75–89
    S5 : Triggered by a calendar event or crisis
    S5 : NPC confronts their inner struggle
    S5 : Full hidden trait revealed
    S5 : Reward: unique cutscene
}

state "Stage 6\nResolution" as S6 {
    S6 : Rel ≥ 90
    S6 : End-of-year moment
    S6 : Player defines relationship type
    S6 : NPC's full arc concluded
    S6 : Reward: memory item, ending slide
}

state "Resolution Type" as RType <<choice>>

state "Close Friendship" as EndFriend {
    EndFriend : Platonic bond\nNPC calls/texts in epilogue
}
state "Romance" as EndRomance {
    EndRomance : Romantic ending\nLong-distance or stay together
}
state "Bittersweet Parting" as EndPart {
    EndPart : Mutual respect\nWistful goodbye scene
}

Stranger    --> S1       : Any interaction triggers acquaintance
S1          --> S2       : Rel ≥ 10 + budding trigger
S2          --> S3       : Rel ≥ 25 + vulnerability trigger
S3          --> S4       : Rel ≥ 50 + trust trigger
S4          --> S5       : Rel ≥ 75 + climax event (calendar-gated)
S5          --> S6       : Rel ≥ 90 + resolution trigger

S6 --> RType
RType --> EndFriend  : Player choice: friendship
RType --> EndRomance : Player choice: romance
RType --> EndPart    : Player choice: respect / goodbye

EndFriend   --> [*]
EndRomance  --> [*]
EndPart     --> [*]

note as NRel
    **Relationship point sources:**
    Dialogue choices: +1 to +5 per interaction
    Shared activities (club, hangout): +3 per session
    Gift giving: +2 to +8 depending on NPC preference
    Helping with tasks: +2 to +5
    Wrong dialogue choice: –1 to –5
    Ignoring NPC for extended time: slow decay (–1/week)
end note

note as NTriggers
    **Stage trigger events are narrative gates:**
    Some triggers require a specific calendar event
    (e.g. Winter Trip, Valentine's Day, exam season).
    NPC arc cannot advance beyond its trigger event
    regardless of relationship score.
end note

@enduml
